Discover a new sense of peace & joy. Let your heart soar with this uplifting night of kirtan.

Weaving together melody, music and mantra with people responding to the words of the singer, clapping, swaying, dancing, kirtan is simultaneously meditative, exhilarating and enjoyable.

Let yourself be immersed in an atmosphere of enchanting sound, lighting and fragrance as the power of chanting meditation gently guides you toward deep inner peace. With each mantra, the stresses of daily life will melt away, and you'll discover a profound sense of connection and solace.

Discover the hidden sanctuary within yourself, where spiritual warmth and comfort reside. No matter how fierce the storms of life may rage outside, they invite you to bask in the transcendental experience that comes from chanting sacred mantras.

A special feature of the evening will be a guided "Journey to Forgiveness" meditation. Afterwards, take time to enjoy tea and connect with like-minded people.

They look forward to sharing this evening of sacred music and spiritual nourishment with you!

Collective Visions will run thru-out July at Old Schoolhouse Gallery and offers a unique blend of styles and mediums.  
Please join the artists for morning tea on the first Sunday of July 
Come along and have a cuppa and a chat with the artists in celebration of this wonderfully vibrant exhibition.  
All works for sale - All welcome.

Collective Visions
Jenny and Jess primarily work in oils and acrylics and have been exhibiting together for over 8 years. Their canvases burst with life celebrating the everyday beauty of still life and the diversity of the Australian outdoors. They will be offering a collection of original paintings on canvas and paper, art prints and cards.

Rhianna is a student at Moreton Bay College and the designer and jewellery-maker behind Joolarhi. Her collection is inspired by Australian landscapes, her love of colour and music, and her heritage. She is looking forward to sharing her collection of wearable art and homewares.
 
They would truly appreciate your support by coming along to see Collective Visions in July, a vibrant showcase of local artistry.
